# Deep Search CLI

Programmatic access to Sourcegraph Deep Search for AI-powered codebase analysis.

## Setup
```bash
export SRC_ACCESS_TOKEN="your-token-here"
export SOURCEGRAPH_URL="https://your-instance.sourcegraph.com"
```

## Commands

### Start new conversation
```bash
ds start --question "Does the repo have authentication middleware?"
```

### Continue existing conversation
```bash
ds ask --id <conversation-id> --question "How does it handle JWT tokens?"
```

### Get conversation by ID
```bash
ds get --id <id>
```

### List conversations
```bash
ds list [--first 5] [--sort -created_at]
```

### Async queries (large codebases)
```bash
ds start --question "Complex question" --async
ds get --id <id>  # poll for results
```

## Multi-Turn Investigation
```bash
CONV_ID=$(ds start --question "What auth methods?" | jq -r '.id')
ds ask --id $CONV_ID --question "How are JWT tokens validated?"
ds ask --id $CONV_ID --question "Where are tokens stored?"
ds get --id $CONV_ID
```

## Best Practices
- Use `--async` for complex questions
- Save conversation IDs for follow-ups
- Structure questions clearly
- Parse JSON with `jq`
- Reuse conversations for follow-ups

